# Langfuse self-host secrets — copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in.
#
# Generate the three crypto values with:
#   openssl rand -hex 32     # ENCRYPTION_KEY  (must be exactly 64 hex chars)
#   openssl rand -base64 32  # SALT
#   openssl rand -base64 32  # NEXTAUTH_SECRET
# Pick strong, distinct passwords for the datastores (any password manager).
# These are bound to 127.0.0.1, but use real secrets anyway — defense in depth.

# --- Langfuse app crypto (REQUIRED, no defaults) ---
LANGFUSE_ENCRYPTION_KEY=    # openssl rand -hex 32   (64 hex chars exactly)
LANGFUSE_SALT=              # openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=            # openssl rand -base64 32

# --- Datastore credentials ---
# Set these ONCE before the first `docker compose up`. Datastores apply their
# password only when initializing an empty volume; changing a value here later
# mismatches the existing volume (auth failures). To rotate: docker compose
# down -v && up -d (discards all traces). See README "Troubleshooting".
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=
CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD=
REDIS_PASSWORD=
MINIO_ROOT_USER=minio
MINIO_ROOT_PASSWORD=
